revision.text:
'''Richard Johnson''' is an American [[gossip columnist]] with the ''[[New York Post]]''{{'}}s Page Six column, which he edited for 25 years. Described by the ''New York Times'' as "a journalistic descendant of [[Walter Winchell]]",<ref>{{cite news|last1=Arango|first1=Tim|title=The Editor of Page Six Is Departing After 25 Years|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/08/business/media/08post.html|work=The New York Times|date=7 October 2010}}</ref> in 1994 he was ranked the No. 1 New York City gossip columnist by ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine in a list that also included [[Liz Smith (journalist)|Liz Smith]], [[Michael Musto]], and [[Cindy Adams]].<ref name="Szabo 1994">{{cite magazine|last1=Szabo|first1=Jlia|title=Gossip, Gossip, and More Gossip|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NeQCAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA22|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|date=August 1, 1994|pages=22–30}}</ref>
Johnson was raised in [[Greenwich Village]], New York, the son of a magazine editor father and a mother who worked in public relations. He attended the [[University of Colorado, Boulder]], and later [[Empire State College]], New York, from which he received a communications degree.<ref name="Payback">{{cite magazine|last1=Grigoriadis|first1=Vanessa|title=Payback|url=http://nymag.com/nymetro/news/features/9503/|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|date=July 19, 2004}}</ref> His first newspaper work was with the ''Chelsea-Clinton News''. He joined the ''New York Post'' in 1978 as a general-assignment reporter, and took charge of Page Six after the departure of editor Susan Mulcahy.<ref name=manhattanmedia/> He worked briefly for the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' in 1991. He left the ''Post'' in 2010 to work in Los Angeles, and returned in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Martin|first1=Adam|title=Richard Johnson Returning to New York As a Post Gossip Columnist|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2013/09/posts-richard-johnson-returning-to-new-york.html|website=[[Daily Intelligencer (New York)|Daily Intelligencer]]|language=en|date=September 11, 2013}}</ref> In 2006 he married Sessa von Richthofen. He was previously married to Nadine Johnson, a New York City publicist.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Handelman|first1=David|title=His & Her Power|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=M-ECAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA31|work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|date=April 22, 1996|pages=24–31}}</ref><ref name="Behind Gossip">{{cite news|last1=Robertson|first1=Campbell|title=Behind Gossip, There's Often a Relationship|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/10/nyregion/behind-gossip-theres-often-a-relationship.html|work=The New York Times|date=April 10, 2006}}</ref><ref name=manhattanmedia>{{cite news|last1=Allon|first1=Janet|title=The Face of Page Six|url=http://www.manhattanmedia.com/pagesix.php|accessdate=4 January 2018|work=[[ManhattanMedia.com]]}}</ref>
